@USANAinc Active Nutrition is here!!🥳 this Electrolyte Replacement is part of it and essential for the summer heat. .Sponsored 

Dressing
* 3 tbsp olive oil
* 3 tbsp lime juice
* 3 garlic clove, minced
* 2 packets Electrolyte Replacement
For the salad
* 5 cups cubed watermelon 
* 1/4 cup Blueberries
* 1/3 Cup Cucumbers
* 1 medium Avocado, cubed 
* 1/2 Serrano Pepper, sliced
* 2 oz. Feta Cheese, crumbled
* mint to taste
* Sea salt and pepper to taste 
Instructions:
Now let’s get started. First whisk together all dressing ingredients. Set aside. 
Assemble the salad ingredients on a platter as desired. Feel free to add or substitute ingredients as you like! Season to taste and serve with dressing. Perfect for the summer!#LiveUSANA  #USANAactive #salad #summer #watermelon #hydrate

Whole30 Creamy Garlic Salmon
By @joyfulhealthyeats 

This Whole30 Creamy Garlic Salmon is the perfect easy dinner! 
Ingredients
* 	4 (4-6oz) salmon filets
* 	2 tablespoons ghee
* 	1 cup yellow onion, diced
* 	1 whole head of garlic, peeled
* 	1 tablespoon lemon juice
* 	1/2 cup chicken broth
* 	15 oz. can of full fat coconut milk, unsweetened
* 	1 teaspoon fresh thyme
* 	1/4 teaspoon salt
* 	1/8 teaspoon black pepper

Instructions
1. Pat salmon filets dry with a paper towel. Season flesh side with salt and pepper.
2. Heat a large skillet to medium high heat. Add 1 tablespoon of ghee and add salmon to skillet skin side down.
3. Pan sear salmon for 4-5 minutes. Gently flip salmon and sear on the flesh side for 2 minutes. Remove salmon from pan and let rest of a plate.
4. Reduce heat to medium, then immediately add remaining tablespoon of ghee and all of your whole garlic cloves. Saute cloves for 3-4 minutes, stirring around the pan occasionally to brown the outside.
5. Once garlic is slightly browned, add yellow onion to pan. Saute for 1-2 minutes, until translucent.
6. Next, add in chicken broth, lemon juice and fresh thyme. Stir and bring to a simmer, reduce by the mixture by half.
7. Slowly add in coconut milk and stir until combined. Season with salt to taste.
8. Add salmon back to pan and simmer for an additional 2 minutes.
9. Garnish with chopped parsley or basil and serve!

FROZEN YOGURT BANANA POPS🍌These cute little pops are everything you didn’t know you needed until now. By @kalejunkie

These are like your favorite chocolate covered bananas, but DIFFERENT, because we're using vanilla-flavored greek yogurt to coat them instead of chocolate. The possibilities for the toppings are endless: you can add sprinkles, melted chocolate, crushed nuts, shredded coconuts, etc. Make them your own! ⁣
Ingredients
* 3 Bananas cut in half
* 1 1/2 Cups Greek Yogurt vanilla flavor
* 1/2 Cup Rainbow Sprinkles
Instructions
* Start by cutting your bananas in half and lining them on a baking sheet. 
* Grab some popsicle sticks and slide one into each half of the banana. 
* Pour some greek yogurt into a bowl, mix until creamy and there are no clumps, then dip each banana pop into it, until they’re fully coated. 
* Put the pops back on the baking sheet and garnish generously with sprinkles. 
* Freeze for two hours or until the greek yogurt solidifies, and enjoy!

KRAPFEN DOUGNUT BAKED OATS 🥵 • EXPLOSIVE 💣 •
By @oatsbaker

You HAVE to try this!

SAVE FOR THE BOMB‼️

dEats🌱
- 1/2 banana
- 50g (1/2 cup) oat flour
- 8–15g (1 tbsp) maple syrup
- 10g (1 tbsp) cashew or nut butter 
- 1/2 tsp baking powder
- 1/3 tsp vanilla extract
- 100/110ml (1/2 cup) nondairy milk
- 70g (1/3 cup) protein vanilla dessert (or vanilla pudding)
- Sprinkle powdered sugar 
Directions⏱ 
- Heat oven to 180 Cº (360 Fº).
- In a bowl mash 1/2 banana and combine with oat flour, maple syrup, cashew butter, vanilla extract and baking powder. Add the nondairy milk and stir.
- Transfer to an ovenproof bowl 3/4 batter and fill with the vanilla protein dessert in the center. Cover with the remaining batter.
- Bake for 20 – 25 minutes.
- Sprinkle with some powdered sugar.

Deutsch 🇩🇪 
- 1/2 Banane
- 50g Hafermehl
- 8-15g Süßungmittel (Ahornsyrup)
- 10g Cashew/ Nussbutter 
- 2.5g Backpulver
- 1/3 TL Vanilleextrakt
- 100/110ml Mandelmilch 
- 70g Proteinpudding (der eine von Aldi/ Lidl, oder Alpro Vanilla Pudding)
Anleitung ⏱ 
- In eine Schale 1/2 Banane (in Puree), Hafermehl, Nussbutter, Süßungmittel, Backpulver, Vanille und Milch zugeben. Alles gut mischen.
- 3/4 Teig in eine oven Bachform zugeben, die Füllung (Proteinpudding) ins Zentrum hinzufügen. Mit etwa mehr Teig bedecken.
- In heißen Oven auf 180 Cº für ca. 25 Minuten backen. 
- Mit Puderzucker dekorieren.

Shrimp Thai ~ Inspired Salad 🌱
Flavor EXPLOSION happening right here you guys! Looking for something quick and flavorful?⬇️ by By @cleanfoodcrush

What You'll need:

A big bunch of various fresh herbs
A few veggies and a pound of raw shrimp 
1 hot skillet to quickly cook your shrimp, and just a few minutes to chop everything up...

What You get: 

A very TASTY, unique meal idea that comes together in minutes, and leaves you feeling AMAZING and full of ENERGY!

Shrimp Thai ~ Inspired Salad is excellent for food prep too! Simply divide everything into four equal servings, then store in sealed containers for up to 2-3 days in your refrigerator.

Ingredients:

For dressing:
4 Tbsps high quality extra virgin olive oil, or sesame seed oil
3 Tbsps white wine vinegar, or apple cider vinegar 
juice of two fresh limes 
2 Tbsps raw honey
2 fresh cloves garlic
1 serrano pepper, seeded
1 cup packed fresh herbs of your choice (mint, basil, cilantro, green onions, parsley)
1/2 tsp sea salt

For the salad:
1 Tbsp olive oil, or avocado oil 
3 cloves fresh garlic, minced
1 serrano pepper, minced
1 lb raw shrimp, peeled and deveined
1 small green cabbage, very thinly sliced
4 cups baby spinach or other greens, roughly chopped 
3 large carrots, peeled and grated
1 cup edamame, shelled and cooked
1/2 cup cashews, roughly chopped
1 Tbsp sesame seeds

Instructions:

In your blender or food processor, pulse all the dressing ingredients until smooth and well combined; refrigerate until ready to use.

Next, heat 1 Tablespoon oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.

Add garlic and the minced serrano pepper, stir-fry for 1 minute just until garlic is fragrant.

Immediately add in your raw shrimp and a pinch of sea salt; cook stirring constantly, turning once, until shrimp become opaque and cooked through, about 3 minutes total.

Remove from the heat and roughly chop them up.

To assemble: place your shredded green cabbage, spinach, carrots and edamame into a salad bowl.

Add shrimp, then drizzle your prepared dressing on top.

Add cashews and toss until all the ingredients are well coated. 

Sprinkle with sesame seeds, then refrigerate for 15 minutes for best flavor.
Enjoy!

Vegan watermelon feta salad perfect for summertime🥰
By @kissmywheatgrass_ 
.
Vegan watermelon feta salad ⏩
INGREDIENTS
2.5 cups of sliced watermelon (into cubes) 
3/4 cup sliced English cucumber 
1/3 cup sliced vegan feta 
1/2 of a lime
Tons of mint 
1-2 tbsps of balsamic vinegar 
1/2 tsp of pepper 
1/2 tsp flakey sea salt 
.
DIRECTIONS
Cut watermelon (I used ~4 of the pre cut triangles) into cubes & add to a large bowl. Peel the skin off of the cucumber, slice into rounds, and then half those rounds and add to the bowl. Cut your bowl of feta into smaller pieces and add those in as well. Then sprinkle in salt & pepper, lots of mint (didn’t measure- just do like a handful or so!!), a tbsp of lime juice, & a tbsp of balsamic vinegar. Mix everything tg. Once you plate it up, top with flakey sea salt & pep then if necessary, more lime or balsamic vinegar (to taste)

ROASTED CHIPOTLE SALMON with FRESH PEACH SALSA!😍 simple and delicious by @kalefornia_kravings

-
For the chipotle salmon:
* 4 salmon fillets, without the skin*
* 1 tsp chili powder
* ¼-½ tsp chipotle chili powder (depending on how spicy you want your salmon)
* ½ tsp paprika
* ½ tsp salt
For the peach salsa:
* 2 large peaches, diced
* ¼ of a red onion, finely chopped
* 2 Tbsp cilantro, chopped
* 2-3 limes, juiced (depending on how "tangy" you want it)
Instructions
To make the salsa:
* Mix the ingredients for your salsa together and keep it chilled in the fridge while you prepare your salmon.  
To make the salmon:
* Preheat your oven to 400 degrees and spray a baking dish with non-stick cooking spray. 
* Mix your spices together and season both sides of your salmon fillets. Place the fillets in your prepared baking dish and bake for 10 minutes. (The salmon should flake easily with a fork once it's done.) 
* Serve immediately with your peach salsa on top.

I love soup and can’t wait to try this one. Italian Wedding Soup 
By @thecozycook

Ingredients
*  1 Tablespoon olive oil
Meatballs
*  ½ lb. ground beef, 80% lean
*  ½ lb. ground pork
*  1 egg, beaten
*  1/2 cup Italian breadcrumbs, homemade is best
*  ¼ cup Parmesan cheese, finely grated into a powder
*  3 cloves garlic, finely diced
*  1/3 cup fresh parsley, roughly chopped
*  salt & freshly ground pepper
Soup
*  1 ¼ cups carrots, diced
*  1 ¼ cups yellow onion, diced
*  ¾ cup celery, diced
*  1 tablespoon garlic, minced
*  8 cups chicken broth,
*  2 teaspoons Italian seasoning
*  salt/pepper
*  ¾ cup acini de pepe pasta, , uncooked
*  8 oz. fresh spinach
To Garnish
*  Fresh parsley, roughly chopped
*  Freshly grated Parmesan cheese

Crock Pot Method
* 	Gently combine the meatball ingredients. Don't overwork the meat. 
* 	Roll the meat into 1-inch balls. 
* 	This Crock Pot allows you to brown the meatballs on the stove top first. I recommend this as the brown bits left on the bottom of the pot transfer lots of flavor into the soup. 
* 	Add the onions, carrots, celery, garlic, chicken broth, Italian seasoning, and browned meatballs. 
* 	Cook on high for 4 hours or low for 8 hours. 
* 	Add the acini de pepe and cook on low for 30 minutes. 
* 	Stir in the Spinach. 
* 	Top with Parmesan cheese, fresh parsley, and serve!
